<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span
 style="font-family: courier new,courier,monospace;">Where and when<a
 name="where"></a></span></h2>
<div style="text-align: justify;"><span
 style="font-family: courier new,courier,monospace;">Group readings
tentatively take place every second wednesday, at 2.00 pm, depending on
availability of volunteers. Topic, room (most often C3 on the II floor
presumably) and speaker will be announced in advance. </span><br
 style="font-family: courier new,courier,monospace;">
<span style="font-family: courier new,courier,monospace;">Lectures take
about 1 and 1/2 hrs and the speaker is expected to cover one topic,
usually the contents of one paper of relevance, providing insight into
the problem considered and the techniques used. Main goal is sitting and
understanding the problem together, so a regular presentation with
slides is not expected. <br>
